reviews.review_text: good quality AUD for download This is a nice high quality AUD. I find this show rather unremarkable. A good blow away, good sailor->truckin, good good. its a gimmee, no jimmy

Hmm... Had I been at this show I would have been bummed out by the obvious exlusion of "Fire" after SB...  But, the "space" is very good, with that odd laughter...  Which was really just a "laughter in a bag" novelty that was popular in the late 70's....

Peaceful Swarm Sugar>Scarlet was a real treat...memorable in its rarity.  Hot & dusty in Buffalo that day...never seen a stadium packed so full..attendance had to be over 100k.  At one point, the crowd started spilling over one wall onto the field...done with peace & unity.
This was last show I saw with Nunes.  Rest in Peace, MN.  Will never forget this one.

The Lauging We stole a creepy doll, a troll magician, from a friend on the way to the show.  Named it "Frank" and went through the lots freaking people out with its manical laughter.  MUHUHUHUHAHAHAHAHAHA-HA-HA-HA! Somehow we lost the doll, friend very mad at us. Then, during space, MUHUHUHUHAHAHAHAHAHA-HA-HA-HA- It's FRANK!!  We were stunned, then told friend it appeared he was not getting the doll back.
what a show!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!! One of my last Crosby stills and nash opened I was blown away by the sugar>>>scarlet>>womens. God wish I could go back
SHIP OF NEWBIE FOOLS? RFK 7/12/90 was the best of the 1990 summer tour but this one wasn't too shabby.  The BREAKDOWN encore just about broke me down, good stuff
